To load the specializations from a database table and display them in a dropdown, you need to follow these steps:
Create the Specialization model and migration

Update the migration file to create the specializations table
$table->id();
            $table->string('name');
            $table->timestamps();

Run the migration to create the table:
php artisan migrate

Create a Seeder for the Specialization Table
php artisan make:seeder SpecializationSeeder

Define Sample Data in the Seeder
namespace Database\Seeders;

use Illuminate\Database\Console\Seeds\WithoutModelEvents;
use Illuminate\Database\Seeder;
use App\Models\Specialization;

class SpecializationSeeder extends Seeder
{
    /**
     * Run the database seeds.
     */
    public function run(): void
    {
        $specializations = [
            ['name' => 'Cardiology'],
            ['name' => 'Neurology'],
            ['name' => 'Pediatrics'],
            ['name' => 'Orthopedics'],
            ['name' => 'Dermatology'],
        ];

        foreach ($specializations as $specialization) {
            Specialization::create($specialization);
        }
    }
}

Run the Seeder
php artisan db:seed --class=SpecializationSeeder

Update the AdminController to load specializations:
use App\Models\Specialization;

public function registerDoctor()
    {
        $specializations = Specialization::all();
        return view('admin.register_doctor', compact('specializations'));
        
    }

