Define the Relationship in the Doctor Model
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Factories\HasFactory;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;

class Doctor extends Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    protected $fillable = [
        'name',
        'specialization',
        'contact_information',
        'dob',
        'nic_number',
        'gender',
    ];

    public function specialization()
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(Specialization::class);
    }
}

If you currently have the specialization field as a string in your doctors table and you want to normalize your database schema by creating a specialization_id foreign key that references the specializations table, you'll need to perform the following steps:

Create a Migration to Add specialization_id Column
php artisan make:migration add_specialization_id_to_doctors_table

Modify the Migration File

public function up(): void
    {
        Schema::table('doctors', function (Blueprint $table) {
            $table->unsignedBigInteger('specialization_id')->nullable();
            $table->foreign('specialization_id')->references('id')->on('specializations');
        });
    }

public function down(): void
    {
        Schema::table('doctors', function (Blueprint $table) {
            $table->dropForeign(['specialization_id']);
            $table->dropColumn('specialization_id');
        });
    }

Update your Doctor model to reflect the new relationship with Specialization.
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Factories\HasFactory;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;

class Doctor extends Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    protected $fillable = [
        'name',
        'specialization_id',
        'contact_information',
        'dob',
        'nic_number',
        'gender',
    ];

    public function specialization()
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(Specialization::class);
    }
}
Create a new migration to remove the specialization field from the doctors table
php artisan make:migration remove_specialization_from_doctors_table

Open the generated migration file and modify it to remove the specialization field.
public function up(): void
    {
        Schema::table('doctors', function (Blueprint $table) {
            $table->dropColumn('specialization');
        });
    }

    /**
     * Reverse the migrations.
     */
    public function down(): void
    {
        Schema::table('doctors', function (Blueprint $table) {
            $table->string('specialization')->nullable();
        });
    }
Run the Migration
php artisan migrate

